On the RPI:
1. Create a new folder called oakstream
2. cd into that folder 
3. run "python3 -m venv .venv"
4. run "source .venv/bin/activate"
5. run "pip install depthai"
6. Go to https://github.com/bluenviron/mediamtx/releases, download 1.19.2 Linux ARM64 package and extract, move both files into under one folder
7. On a terminal, run ./mediamtx 
8. Create a python script inside oakstream, copy and paste from oakstream.py on this github
9. On a terminal, run oakstream.py, it will give you a rtsp://localhost link
10. Run hostname -I to get your RPI IP, replace localhost with your IP so you can open up the stream on other machine